	)
	)
	(text "POWER  --  1S LiPo -> TPS63001 buck-boost -> 3V3"
		(at 10 190 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "c83ae485-75cc-4ee4-8e1c-4dd0b759e63c")
	)
	(text "+3V3 is the single regulated logic rail: the ESP32-S3 module, mux logic, encoder VCC,\nphototransistor pull-ups, indicator drivers and IR LED current all come from here."
		(at 200 100 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.2 2.2)))
		(uuid "e64bb1c5-eae1-4baa-9233-28e9e7b1b693")
	)
	(text "VBAT_SENSE = cell voltage (0-4.2V) scaled to <=2.52V by 22k/33k (the S3 ADC calibrated\nrange tops at ~2.9V with worst error near the top -- keep headroom). Into ADC1 IO8.\nFirmware low-battery cutoff at 3.0V/cell. Single 1S cell: no balance lead."
		(at 20 20 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.2 2.2)))
		(uuid "0351d267-4402-4037-abd3-3a4bef0e9241")
	)
	(text "MOTOR DRIVER (TB6612FNG, SMD)  --  2x N20-with-encoder motors"
		(at 10 230 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "b0c7b221-d0f0-44d3-9aea-ab2a986a0ad8")
	)
	(text "Bare TB6612FNG (U2, SSOP-24): STBY/AIN/BIN plain GPIO, PWMA/PWMB = LEDC.\nVM = raw 1S cell (2.5V min OK), VCC = +3V3. Doubled pins (AO1/AO2/BO1/BO2 pairs,\nPGND pairs, VM triple) are bridged by the router's micro-bridge pass.\nDecoupling at the chip: C11 10uF + C12 100nF on VM, C14 100nF on VCC."
		(at 10 258 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "3c2dc7f6-979d-4dde-8c5f-0d6e39da6684")
	)
	(text "10k pull-ups on all 4 encoder lines -- defensive: N20-encoder wire-color-to-\nfunction mapping is unverified for the exact unit ordered (see PROJECT_NOTES.md),\nand encoder output stage (open-drain vs push-pull) isn't confirmed either. A pull-up\nis required if open-drain and harmless if push-pull.\nMotor connector pin order is FUNCTIONAL (M+,M-,ENC_VCC,ENC_GND,ENC_A,ENC_B) --\nverify against the real wire-to-pin mapping at assembly time, not assumed here."
		(at 10 400 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "b5d68ef0-0849-4118-a65b-fd8748d4e929")
	)
	(text "CONTROLLER  --  ESP32-S3-WROOM-1 (dual-core 240MHz, FreeRTOS, WiFi): control + telemetry"
		(at 300 230 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "212cbfab-f456-4896-825f-e30a9d471229")
	)
	(text "ESP32-S3-WROOM-1 on FreeRTOS: 6 wall sensors DIRECT on ADC1 IO1-IO6 (a fired pair is\nsampled in parallel), line array via U4 (IO7 + IO11-13), battery IO8, TB6612 on\nIO9/10/18/21/38/45/46 (straps 45/46 = idle-low outputs ONLY -- never add pull-ups),\nencoders IO43/44/47/48 (PCNT hardware quadrature via GPIO matrix), JTAG on the real\nJTAG quad IO39-42 -> J8 (ESP-Prog). Buttons: SW1=IO0 (start/BOOT), SW3=IO35, SW4=IO36\n(internal pull-ups). USB-C (rear) on the native USB pads = flash + console; UART0\npins repurposed as encoder inputs. Every analog net sits on ADC1 (IO1-IO8)."
		(at 300 368 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "6574390f-2ef5-45da-a69f-6c115c65773b")
	)
	(text "USER INTERFACE  --  3 buttons"
		(at 600 230 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "7709bfdd-fb90-4ead-8e58-46eac6d37cfd")
	)
	(text "Buttons are lettered on the silkscreen: A=SW1, B=SW3, C=SW4, RST=SW2.\nSW1/A = USER_BTN on IO0: start-run button AND the BOOT strap (hold A, tap RST\n-> ROM download mode). External 10k pull-up R10 keeps the strap solid.\nSW3/SW4 = USER_BTN2/3 on IO35/IO36 (menu/select UX): active-low, firmware enables the\ninternal pull-ups -- no external resistors. NOTE: on octal-PSRAM (-R8) modules IO35/36\ndo not exist; buttons 2/3 are the sacrificial feature (control is unaffected).\nSW2 (reset) lives in the controller section on ESP_EN."
		(at 600 260 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "00258556-40c9-403c-a404-407bcb02339a")
	)
	(text "IR SENSOR ARRAY  --  6 wall + 8 line sensors"
		(at 10 420 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "fb91c2b3-b8ac-47ce-9c31-1bf9323534be")
	)
	(text "ONE HEF4067 (line array only -- user decision 2026-07-15: wall sensors are read\ndirectly on ESP32 ADC1 pins). Each sensor: phototransistor (collector -> 47k pull-up\nto +3V3 AND to its readout node; emitter -> GND) + IR LED (anode -> current-limit\nresistor -> +3V3; cathode -> its GROUP's low-side switch). Emitters are GANGED:\nfront pair / diagonal pair / side pair / all-8 line bank, each on one BSS138 driven\nby its own GPIO (IO15/16/17/14). Firing a wall pair and sampling BOTH its ADC pins\nin the same pulse halves scan time vs the old serial mux walk; read bright, read\nambient (group off), subtract. Current-limit: wall 33R (~50mA pulsed) / line 120R\n(~15mA, latch-capable for line-follow + indicators). UKMARS-practice grouping keeps\nmutually-staring sensors on different groups."
		(at 150 460 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "2b037acc-2c86-4ec5-97da-29bd0adc0f84")
	)
	(text "LINE-SENSOR INDICATORS  --  8 top-side LEDs, one per line channel"
		(at 10 640 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "4b577df6-12bf-484a-b801-a3e3723d1d8a")
	)
	(text "BSS138 gate on each LINEx_SENSE node (zero DC load: gate leakage <=100nA worst-case = ~5mV\non the 47k divider; if one channel ever reads pinned, suspect its Q30-Q37 gate). Drain sinks\na super-red 0603 from +3V3 via 1k (~1.4mA). In practice a THRESHOLD indicator: the BSS138's\n~150-300mV dark-to-full band makes it crisp on/off around ~1.2V -- ideal for reading line\nposition across 8 LEDs at a glance. LED ON = dark line under that sensor.\nFIRMWARE RULE: indicators are only meaningful while the line emitters are LIT -- pulsed\nscanning leaves the node ambient-dominated ~93% of the time. Line emitters are 120R\n(~15mA), sized so line-follow mode can latch all 8 on continuously (~120mA)."
		(at 10 655 0)
		(effects (font (size 2.0 2.0)))
		(uuid "22a3da3d-fa58-4eb3-a14f-0e9f1ebadad2")
	)
	(text "WALL-SENSOR INDICATORS  --  6 top-side LEDs, LED ON = wall seen (PMOS, inverted node)"
		(at 10 760 0)
		(effects (font (size 5 5)))
		(uuid "4eaaa6c0-e74e-4bf8-bb4e-58c477980320")
	)
